1
00:00:04,740 --> 00:00:06,080
I think bread is like a dream.

2
00:00:09,980 --> 00:00:12,250
At the moment, it's my everything.

3
00:00:14,320 --> 00:00:17,050
This is the first baking survival program.

4
00:00:20,520 --> 00:00:23,430
I've waited for a baking contest like this for a long time.

5
00:00:25,060 --> 00:00:26,699
K-pop? Yes.

6
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:28,369
K-drama? Yes.

7
00:00:28,370 --> 00:00:29,870
K-food? Yes.

8
00:00:31,030 --> 00:00:32,670
With K-bread,

9
00:00:33,540 --> 00:00:36,140
I believe it'll create a bigger impact than K-wave.

10
00:00:38,610 --> 00:00:40,480
My heart flutters.

11
00:00:40,880 --> 00:00:42,480
I look forward to it very much.

12
00:00:46,820 --> 00:00:51,360
Korean bread is taking the world by storm.

13
00:00:52,360 --> 00:00:55,129
(This video is AI-generated.)

14
00:00:55,130 --> 00:00:57,060
Amid this massive trend,

15
00:00:58,160 --> 00:01:01,770
who will be the best baker...

16
00:01:03,170 --> 00:01:05,440
to represent the next generation?

17
00:01:19,750 --> 00:01:23,289
We dream of making a new history...

18
00:01:23,290 --> 00:01:25,260
where Korean bread sets the global standard.

19
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:27,320
Bake Your Dream.

20
00:01:27,890 --> 00:01:31,900
There are 72 contestants who will bake their dreams...

21
00:01:32,060 --> 00:01:35,130
here in this bread factory of Bake Your Dream.

22
00:01:35,870 --> 00:01:37,070
We'll reveal them now.

23
00:01:49,450 --> 00:01:50,450
(Masters in the shadows)

24
00:01:50,451 --> 00:01:52,220
It requires a high degree of skills.

25
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:55,290
Those with less than ten years of experience will find it hard.

26
00:01:56,550 --> 00:01:59,660
I don't think they can keep up with my expertise.

27
00:02:01,490 --> 00:02:03,730
I think a trend is a different matter.

28
00:02:03,990 --> 00:02:05,729
(Super rookies)

29
00:02:05,730 --> 00:02:06,730
I'm fearless.

30
00:02:09,070 --> 00:02:11,500
I believe I'm not behind anyone when it comes to baking.

31
00:02:14,540 --> 00:02:16,410
No one can outrun me.

32
00:02:18,180 --> 00:02:19,810
I'm a pastry chef from Italy...

33
00:02:20,180 --> 00:02:21,279
and a three-star baker.

34
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:22,280
(Foreign bakers to conquer K-bread)

35
00:02:22,281 --> 00:02:25,750
I work at InterContinental Paris Le Grand Hotel.

36
00:02:26,920 --> 00:02:30,090
Don't you think French bread would taste better?

37
00:02:31,490 --> 00:02:34,859
Bread is a daily staple here.

38
00:02:34,860 --> 00:02:36,090
So, no worries.

39
00:02:37,590 --> 00:02:39,299
Taegeukdang and Napoleon.

40
00:02:39,300 --> 00:02:40,399
Leesungdang in Gunsan.

41
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:41,600
Richemont.

42
00:02:41,630 --> 00:02:43,999
I worked at Sungsimdang.

43
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,000
(Must-visit hot places for bread)

44
00:02:46,670 --> 00:02:48,610
It's bread with my own unique style,

45
00:02:49,170 --> 00:02:50,510
so I think it'll give me an edge.

46
00:02:52,710 --> 00:02:54,750
I love competitions like this.

47
00:02:55,350 --> 00:02:57,750
My final goal is to win first place.

48
00:02:59,720 --> 00:03:00,850
I'm confident.

49
00:03:02,150 --> 00:03:04,690
(A battle of 72 bakers for one bread)

50
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:08,159
(The battle of bread...)

51
00:03:08,160 --> 00:03:09,590
(has finally begun.)

52
00:03:10,330 --> 00:03:11,430
It's crazy.

53
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:13,900
Isn't this a battleground that's made for me?

54
00:03:14,030 --> 00:03:15,400
(Amazed)

55
00:03:15,570 --> 00:03:17,199
- It's awesome. - It's crazy.

56
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:20,200
(The competition venue of overwhelming scale)

57
00:03:22,070 --> 00:03:23,470
Half of us will be eliminated?

58
00:03:23,940 --> 00:03:25,579
I don't want to lose.

59
00:03:25,580 --> 00:03:27,080
My competitive spirit is rising.

60
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:31,449
(But...)

61
00:03:31,450 --> 00:03:33,580
Gosh, it's so frustrating.

62
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:35,950
Darn it. It's not working out.

63
00:03:36,990 --> 00:03:38,760
It's burnt. This isn't easy.

64
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:43,960
(Never-ending tension and pressure)

65
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:46,059
(Prove...)

66
00:03:46,060 --> 00:03:47,060
(yourself...)

67
00:03:47,061 --> 00:03:48,870
(with bread.)

68
00:03:49,070 --> 00:03:52,070
I find baking bread so much fun.

69
00:03:52,870 --> 00:03:54,640
I'm really thankful for this bread.

70
00:03:55,210 --> 00:03:57,910
But it feels like it's holding me back. I hate it.

71
00:03:59,310 --> 00:04:02,010
I can't stop crying when I talk about it.

72
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:03,810
Sorry.

73
00:04:13,060 --> 00:04:15,159
- Hey. It's going to be tough. - What?

74
00:04:15,160 --> 00:04:16,460
- It'll be tough. - Yes.

75
00:04:17,060 --> 00:04:18,330
Gosh. It isn't easy.

76
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:23,070
Now, let me introduce to you...

77
00:04:23,170 --> 00:04:26,140
Bake Your Dream's Masters who will be your judges.

78
00:04:36,610 --> 00:04:40,820
(The Masters of Bake Your Dream)

79
00:04:40,880 --> 00:04:42,149
Gosh. It's Kwon Sung Jun.

80
00:04:42,150 --> 00:04:43,290
It's Napoli Matfia.

81
00:04:44,320 --> 00:04:45,989
Gosh. It's Kwon Sung Jun.

82
00:04:45,990 --> 00:04:47,120
He was in "Culinary Class Wars."

83
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:50,230
Gosh. It's Noh Hee Young.

84
00:04:55,530 --> 00:04:58,700
I was shocked to see Chef Kim Narae there.

85
00:05:04,780 --> 00:05:08,550
She's like a huge idol to us.

86
00:05:09,010 --> 00:05:10,810
It's an honor to be judged by her.

87
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:14,449
(It's Pastry Chef Kim Narae.)

88
00:05:14,450 --> 00:05:16,149
(She was the first Asian woman to be chosen...)

89
00:05:16,150 --> 00:05:18,159
(as the French pastry chef of the year in 2024.)

90
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:19,819
("Narae from Dangjin, South Chungcheong Province...")

91
00:05:19,820 --> 00:05:21,489
("Creates an Uproar in Paris")

92
00:05:21,490 --> 00:05:22,960
("Korean Kim Narae to be Chosen as the Best French Pastry Chef")

93
00:05:23,330 --> 00:05:26,329
As a woman and as an Asian,

94
00:05:26,330 --> 00:05:28,569
it wasn't easy for me to work in the kitchen.

95
00:05:28,570 --> 00:05:31,099
I want to express my sincere gratitude...

96
00:05:31,100 --> 00:05:34,200
to Gault and Milau for giving me the opportunity.

97
00:05:34,270 --> 00:05:36,339
(She works as an executive pastry chef...)

98
00:05:36,340 --> 00:05:38,879
(at Hotel H in France, a paradise for desserts,)

99
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:41,380
(creating stylish and artistic desserts.)

100
00:05:41,650 --> 00:05:43,679
(She also participated as a judge...)

101
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:45,720
(for Coupe du Monde de la Patisserie in 2025.)

102
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:48,290
(Kim Narae, a world-class pastry chef)

103
00:05:48,450 --> 00:05:51,089
Why are you using flour, not oil, to spread it?

104
00:05:51,090 --> 00:05:52,960
- You put oil in the dough, right? - Yes.

105
00:05:53,260 --> 00:05:54,860
Aren't you going to measure it?

106
00:05:56,890 --> 00:05:59,230
(Master Kim Narae doesn't compromise when it comes to flavors.)

107
00:05:59,330 --> 00:06:03,069
As I'm based in France, the homeland of baking,

108
00:06:03,070 --> 00:06:06,899
I'll strictly judge the flavors of the bread,

109
00:06:06,900 --> 00:06:10,270
focusing on whether K-bakeries can be globalized.

110
00:06:12,540 --> 00:06:14,809
Hello, I'm Lee Seok Won,

111
00:06:14,810 --> 00:06:16,549
Korea's 17th Master Pastry Chef.

112
00:06:16,550 --> 00:06:18,850
(I'm Master Craftman Lee Seok Won.)

113
00:06:20,420 --> 00:06:21,749
(Master Craftman)

114
00:06:21,750 --> 00:06:22,819
(A title awarded to master artisans with outstanding expertise...)

115
00:06:22,820 --> 00:06:24,149
(across 92 professions in 38 categories in Korea)

116
00:06:24,150 --> 00:06:26,819
(As for Master Pastry Chef,)

117
00:06:26,820 --> 00:06:30,260
(only 17 people were awarded with the title as of 2026.)

118
00:06:30,590 --> 00:06:31,729
(The 17th and the youngest Master Pastry Chef in 2024)

119
00:06:31,730 --> 00:06:33,159
("Korea's youngest Master Pastry Chef, Lee Seok Won")

120
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:35,429
He was awarded the 17th Master Pastry Chef.

121
00:06:35,430 --> 00:06:38,539
As far as I know, not many people are awarded as Masters.

122
00:06:38,540 --> 00:06:40,440
And he's the youngest to be a Master.

123
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:43,169
In this field,

124
00:06:43,170 --> 00:06:45,980
he was named the youngest of everything.

125
00:06:46,080 --> 00:06:48,680
(He was the youngest executive chef of Sungsimdang.)

126
00:06:48,850 --> 00:06:50,179
(He was the youngest to earn the Korean Master Baker title...)

127
00:06:50,180 --> 00:06:51,510
(in 2004 at the age of 29.)

128
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:54,550
(Master Lee Seok Won with the highest authority)

129
00:06:54,780 --> 00:06:56,890
Korea isn't the birthplace of bread.

130
00:06:56,990 --> 00:06:58,559
But the reputation of Korean bakeries...

131
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:00,920
has been increasing lately.

132
00:07:01,460 --> 00:07:03,429
Our skills have developed to the point...

133
00:07:03,430 --> 00:07:06,630
where we can stand on the podium alongside other European countries.

134
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:09,629
We have to identify talents...

135
00:07:09,630 --> 00:07:11,599
that will lead Korean bakeries.

136
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:14,699
I will consider their potential to grow in mind...

137
00:07:14,700 --> 00:07:16,170
when judging them.

138
00:07:17,410 --> 00:07:19,980
Master Noh Hee Young, could you say a few words?

139
00:07:20,310 --> 00:07:23,910
Hello, I'm Noh Hee Young, a woman who makes brands.

140
00:07:25,380 --> 00:07:28,180
She's a godmother of branding.

141
00:07:28,490 --> 00:07:29,889
I signed up for her branding lecture,

142
00:07:29,890 --> 00:07:32,420
not knowing she'd be here.

143
00:07:32,790 --> 00:07:35,659
While developing countless brands,

144
00:07:35,660 --> 00:07:37,960
I've tasted everything out there.

145
00:07:38,130 --> 00:07:39,759
It looks pretty.

146
00:07:39,760 --> 00:07:40,929
(But it's very disappointing.)

147
00:07:40,930 --> 00:07:42,730
(It's like the bread from 20 years ago.)

148
00:07:42,770 --> 00:07:45,370
It's hard to be open-minded even though I've tried.

149
00:07:46,170 --> 00:07:48,910
(Evaluating market values strictly as an FnB legend)

150
00:07:49,070 --> 00:07:50,439
Based on my extensive experience,

151
00:07:50,440 --> 00:07:52,779
I'll see if the contestants' bread and desserts...

152
00:07:52,780 --> 00:07:55,049
can be expanded as a brand.

153
00:07:55,050 --> 00:07:56,710
That's what I'll focus on when judging.

154
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:00,379
Master Kwon Sung Jun, could you say a few words?

155
00:08:00,380 --> 00:08:01,580
Yes. Hello.

156
00:08:01,820 --> 00:08:02,849
(The winner of "Culinary Class Wars: Season 1")

157
00:08:02,850 --> 00:08:03,919
("Black Spoon Kwon Sung Jun Beats Edward Lee...")

158
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:05,160
("and Wins 300,000 Dollars")

159
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:08,260
(Chosen by Forbes in 2025)

160
00:08:08,660 --> 00:08:12,460
(A ruthless fighter of flavors)

161
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:15,670
(Italian Chef Kwon Sung Jun)

162
00:08:15,770 --> 00:08:17,569
As you may all know,

163
00:08:17,570 --> 00:08:19,969
at this very place,

164
00:08:19,970 --> 00:08:23,209
I participated in a competition as a contestant.

165
00:08:23,210 --> 00:08:26,310
That's why I believe I understand better than anyone...

166
00:08:26,610 --> 00:08:28,780
about how you feel to be here.

167
00:08:29,010 --> 00:08:31,109
I'm not an expert in baking,

168
00:08:31,110 --> 00:08:33,679
but I do make bread and desserts every day at my restaurant.

169
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:35,719
So, I feel like I'm here to learn.

170
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:37,519
I'll focus on the storytelling, characters,

171
00:08:37,520 --> 00:08:40,259
and uniqueness when it comes to judging.

172
00:08:40,260 --> 00:08:41,260
I look forward to it.

173
00:08:43,290 --> 00:08:46,660
I think he'd understand us better than anyone.

174
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,670
Please say something, Master Mimi.

175
00:08:51,130 --> 00:08:53,169
Yes. Hello, everyone. I'm Mimi.

176
00:08:53,170 --> 00:08:54,270
(Master Mimi)

177
00:08:56,170 --> 00:08:59,280
(Is Mimi a master?)

178
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:04,780
(She has mastered every hot bakery item.)

179
00:09:05,220 --> 00:09:07,780
(Her nickname is even Dessert Queen.)

180
00:09:08,650 --> 00:09:12,690
(She's a celebrity well-known for her love for bread.)

181
00:09:12,820 --> 00:09:14,559
It's divine.

182
00:09:14,560 --> 00:09:17,029
For some reason, I thought Mimi would be here...

183
00:09:17,030 --> 00:09:19,559
because she loves desserts so much.

184
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:21,130
Being a bread lover.

185
00:09:21,430 --> 00:09:23,170
It's not an easy thing to do.

186
00:09:23,730 --> 00:09:25,540
Please get ready for the power of the bread fanatic.

187
00:09:27,340 --> 00:09:29,270
(Bake Your Dream)

188
00:09:29,540 --> 00:09:31,710
(A group of 5 masters with 5 characters is ready.)

189
00:09:31,980 --> 00:09:34,979
Now, the epic journey to find...

190
00:09:34,980 --> 00:09:38,210
the one bread that will rule the world.

191
00:09:38,780 --> 00:09:40,180
Bake Your Dream.

192
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:43,950
Bake Your Dream will begin now.

193
00:09:44,090 --> 00:09:45,320
(Bake Your Dream begins.)

194
00:09:46,490 --> 00:09:48,690
(Bake Your Dream)

195
00:09:56,830 --> 00:09:59,069
The final winner of Bake Your Dream...

196
00:09:59,070 --> 00:10:00,999
will get a total prize money of 100,000 dollars,

197
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,640
a chance to launch a brand,

198
00:10:02,910 --> 00:10:05,340
and a high-end electrical SUV...

199
00:10:05,710 --> 00:10:08,710
that will support your dream.

200
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:29,930
- Gosh. - Goodness.

201
00:10:30,970 --> 00:10:32,070
Gosh.

202
00:10:33,170 --> 00:10:34,399
Goodness.

203
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:35,570
The set is huge.

204
00:10:36,340 --> 00:10:38,840
I thought, "It's really beginning."

205
00:10:39,440 --> 00:10:41,080
Gosh. Look at the equipment.

206
00:10:42,510 --> 00:10:44,249
- It's amazing. - Gosh.

207
00:10:44,250 --> 00:10:45,350
It's crazy. Gosh.

208
00:10:46,820 --> 00:10:49,190
It felt overwhelming.

209
00:10:49,520 --> 00:10:52,290
I was shocked because it was bigger than I expected.

210
00:10:55,890 --> 00:10:56,990
It's crazy.

211
00:11:01,260 --> 00:11:04,800
(The contestants find their places.)

212
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:14,410
(A subtle tension builds up in the bread factory.)

213
00:11:19,350 --> 00:11:20,550
I was so scared.

214
00:11:25,320 --> 00:11:27,190
It's real.

215
00:11:28,160 --> 00:11:29,330
Here we go now.

216
00:11:29,860 --> 00:11:31,060
Here it begins.

217
00:11:32,260 --> 00:11:33,700
I'm very nervous.

218
00:11:35,730 --> 00:11:38,000
I feel more excited than nervous.

219
00:11:38,430 --> 00:11:40,700
I thought, "Can there be anyone better than me?"

220
00:11:45,940 --> 00:11:48,180
Okay. Welcome, Contestants.

221
00:11:48,710 --> 00:11:50,410
This is the place...

222
00:11:50,650 --> 00:11:53,220
you will have your competition.

223
00:11:57,090 --> 00:12:00,520
Now, I will announce the mission for Round One.

224
00:12:01,160 --> 00:12:03,160
For Round One of Bake Your Dream,

225
00:12:06,460 --> 00:12:08,630
you'll bake your signature bread.

226
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:10,630
(Round 1: Bake Your Signature Bread)

227
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:17,740
You'll make bread that reflects your unique baking journey...

228
00:12:18,010 --> 00:12:20,140
and that represents you.

229
00:12:20,310 --> 00:12:21,509
With the bread, you'll prove...

230
00:12:21,510 --> 00:12:24,380
why you need to survive Bake Your Dream.

231
00:12:24,780 --> 00:12:27,180
Half of the contestants who fail to prove their abilities...

232
00:12:27,650 --> 00:12:28,750
will be eliminated.

233
00:12:32,220 --> 00:12:33,619
I actually loved the idea...

234
00:12:33,620 --> 00:12:35,459
because my bread is really lovely.

235
00:12:35,460 --> 00:12:39,629
As soon as I heard it, I thought it was something I could do well.

236
00:12:39,630 --> 00:12:41,359
I thought I should let them taste...

237
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:43,470
the bread served in my shop as is.

238
00:12:43,570 --> 00:12:44,929
I was just confident.

239
00:12:44,930 --> 00:12:46,499
It's hard to sell our bread...

240
00:12:46,500 --> 00:12:47,900
because it's always sold out.

241
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:51,710
I'll reveal the judging process of Round One.

242
00:12:53,740 --> 00:12:56,380
They only have four hours.

243
00:12:58,080 --> 00:13:01,819
The bread will be judged in the order of completion.

244
00:13:01,820 --> 00:13:03,049
(Within 4 hours, it'll be judged in the order of completion.)

245
00:13:03,050 --> 00:13:04,489
When the contestant puts the finished bread...

246
00:13:04,490 --> 00:13:06,189
on the conveyor belt...

247
00:13:06,190 --> 00:13:07,819
(The finished bread goes to the evaluation room on the belt.)

248
00:13:07,820 --> 00:13:09,730
Then it's delivered to the masters' table.

249
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:12,230
And the evaluation begins.

250
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:15,269
The first bread is coming.

251
00:13:15,270 --> 00:13:16,430
My goodness!

252
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:19,640
Gosh.

253
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:23,469
After the evaluation,

254
00:13:23,470 --> 00:13:27,280
five masters choose a pass or a fail on their tablet PCs.

255
00:13:27,540 --> 00:13:30,079
The contestant can only advance to the next round...

256
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:32,520
when a majority of the masters give them a pass.

257
00:13:36,050 --> 00:13:38,890
Okay. Round One...

258
00:13:39,160 --> 00:13:41,520
of Bake Your Dream,

259
00:13:41,990 --> 00:13:44,260
the mission of baking your signature bread,

260
00:13:44,490 --> 00:13:46,860
will begin now.

261
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:48,670
Good luck!

262
00:13:48,930 --> 00:13:49,970
Go!

263
00:13:50,430 --> 00:13:51,570
Let's go.

264
00:13:52,340 --> 00:13:53,599
(Judging process for Round 1)

265
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:55,199
(The 72 contestants...)

266
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:56,440
